.TH DIALTOR 1 "2026-05-01" "dialtor 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dialtor \- Advanced Tor network control CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dialtor
[\fIGLOBAL OPTIONS\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fICOMMAND OPTIONS\fR]
[\fIARGUMENTS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dialtor
is a professional command-line tool for managing Tor network connections, circuits, and relays. It provides fine-grained control over Tor circuits, identity rotation, relay selection, bridge configuration, and onion services.
.PP
.B dialtor
connects to the local Tor daemon via the control port and uses the Tor control protocol to manage network operations. It can be used both as a CLI tool and as a Python library for automation.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Connection Management
.TP
.B connect verify
Connect to Tor daemon and verify network status
.SS Circuit Control
.TP
.B circuit list
List all active Tor circuits
.TP
.B circuit create
Create a new circuit with optional country/relay selection
.TP
.B circuit info \fICIRCUIT-ID\fR
Show detailed information about a specific circuit
.TP
.B circuit close \fICIRCUIT-ID\fR
Close a specific circuit
.SS Identity Management
.TP
.B identity new
Request a new Tor identity (NEWNYM signal)
.TP
.B identity rotate
Close circuits older than specified age
.TP
.B identity status
Show current identity information
.SS Relay Management
.TP
.B relay list
List and filter Tor relays by country, flags, or bandwidth
.TP
.B relay info \fIFINGERPRINT\fR
Show detailed information about a specific relay
.SS Bridge Configuration
.TP
.B bridge add \fIBRIDGE-LINE\fR
Add a bridge for censorship circumvention
.TP
.B bridge list
List configured bridges
.TP
.B bridge test \fIADDRESS\fR \fIPORT\fR
Test bridge connectivity
.TP
.B bridge remove \fIADDRESS\fR \fIPORT\fR
Remove a configured bridge
.TP
.B bridge clear
Remove all bridges
.SS Onion Services
.TP
.B onion create
Create a new ephemeral onion service (v3)
.TP
.B onion list
List active onion services
.TP
.B onion info \fISERVICE-ID\fR
Show onion service details
.TP
.B onion remove \fISERVICE-ID\fR
Remove an onion service
.SS Scripting
.TP
.B script run \fISCRIPT-PATH\fR
Execute a Python automation script
.TP
.B script list
List available example scripts
.TP
.B script show \fISCRIPT-NAME\fR
Display source code of an example script
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-install\-completion \fISHELL\fR
Install shell completion for bash, zsh, or fish
.TP
.B \-\-show\-completion \fISHELL\fR
Show completion script without installing
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic Usage
Verify Tor connection:
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor connect verify
.RE
.fi
.PP
List active circuits:
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor circuit list
.RE
.fi
.PP
Create circuit with US exit node:
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor circuit create \-\-exit\-country US
.RE
.fi
.SS Advanced Relay Selection
List fast German relays:
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor relay list \-\-country DE \-\-flags Fast,Stable
.RE
.fi
.PP
Filter relays by bandwidth (minimum 5 MB/s):
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor relay list \-\-min\-bandwidth 5242880
.RE
.fi
.SS Identity Management
Request new identity:
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor identity new
.RE
.fi
.PP
Close circuits older than 10 minutes:
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor identity rotate \-\-max\-age 600
.RE
.fi
.SS Bridge Configuration
Add obfs4 bridge:
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor bridge add "obfs4 192.0.2.1:9001 AAAA1111... cert=abcd,iat\-mode=0"
.RE
.fi
.SS Onion Services
Create onion service for local web server:
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor onion create \-\-virtual\-port 80 \-\-target\-port 8080
.RE
.fi
.SS Automation
Run automation script:
.PP
.nf
.RS
dialtor script run auto_rotate
.RE
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.dialtor/config.toml
User configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.config/dialtor/config.toml
Alternative configuration location
.TP
.I /etc/dialtor/config.toml
System-wide configuration
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DIALTOR_CONTROL_PORT
Override Tor control port (default: 9051)
.TP
.B DIALTOR_PASSWORD
Tor control port password
.TP
.B DIALTOR_LOG_LEVEL
Logging level (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR)
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B dialtor
reads configuration from TOML files in the following order:
.IP 1. 4
~/.dialtor/config.toml
.IP 2.
~/.config/dialtor/config.toml
.IP 3.
/etc/dialtor/config.toml
.PP
Environment variables override configuration file settings.
.PP
Example configuration:
.PP
.nf
.RS
[connection]
control_port = 9051
password = "your_password_here"
timeout = 30

[relay_selection]
preferred_countries = ["us", "de", "nl"]
min_bandwidth = 1048576
required_flags = ["Fast", "Stable"]

[logging]
level = "INFO"
.RE
.fi
.SH PREREQUISITES
.TP
.B Tor daemon
Must be running and accessible on control port (default: 9051)
.TP
.B Python 3.10+
Required for running dialtor
.PP
Install Tor:
.PP
.B macOS:
brew install tor && brew services start tor
.PP
.B Ubuntu/Debian:
sudo apt-get install tor && sudo systemctl start tor
